headline: What Humana (HUM)'s Profit Drop and Lowered Outlook Mean For Shareholders
summary: In early November 2025, Humana Inc. reported third quarter results showing increased revenue to US$32.65 billion, but net income dropped to US$195 million compared to the previous year. The company also completed a US$200 million share buyback and revised its 2025 annual earnings guidance downward to approximately US$12.26 per share.
